## Part 2: The Regulatory Portal Vision

### 2.1 Design Philosophy

The Regulatory Portal is not a separate product — it's a **compliance intelligence layer** that sits on top of EduPod's existing modules and transforms raw operational data into regulatory submissions, deadline tracking, and compliance dashboards.

**Key principles:**
1. **Zero re-entry** — Every regulatory submission should be auto-populated from data already in EduPod
2. **Deadline-driven** — The regulatory calendar drives proactive alerts, not reactive fire-fighting
3. **Validation-first** — Pre-submission validation catches errors before they reach government systems
4. **Audit trail** — Every submission is logged, versioned, and downloadable for inspection readiness
5. **Progressive disclosure** — School admins see a clean compliance dashboard; the complexity is hidden

### 2.2 Proposed Module Architecture

```
Regulatory Portal (new top-level nav item)
├── Compliance Dashboard           ← Single pane of glass
│   ├── Calendar view (all deadlines)
│   ├── Status cards per domain
│   └── Alerts & Overdue items
│
├── DES Returns                    ← Tier 1 (non-negotiable)
│   ├── September Returns (Files A–E)
│   ├── Form TL (auto from timetabling)
│   ├── DTR Subject Codes
│   └── October Returns / Census
│
├── P-POD / POD                    ← Tier 1 (non-negotiable)
│   ├── Student Data Sync
│   ├── CBA Result Upload (post-primary)
│   ├── October Returns
│   ├── Sync Status & Error Log
│   └── Transfer Management
│
├── Tusla Reporting                ← Tier 1 (non-negotiable)
│   ├── Absence Threshold Monitor
│   ├── Student Absence Reports (SAR)
│   ├── Annual Attendance Report (AAR)
│   ├── Suspension/Expulsion Notifications
│   ├── Reduced School Day Register
│   └── Educational Welfare Referrals
│
├── Child Safeguarding             ← Tier 1 (non-negotiable)
│   ├── Safeguarding Statement Status
│   ├── DLP Register
│   ├── Mandated Report Log
│   └── Annual Review Tracker
│
├── Anti-Bullying (Bí Cineálta)   ← Tier 1 (from Sept 2025)
│   ├── Incident Register (links to Behaviour module)
│   ├── Board Meeting Reports (auto-generated)
│   ├── Annual DES Submission
│   └── Policy Review Tracker
│
├── Financial Compliance           ← Tier 2 (important)
│   ├── FSSU Annual Accounts Export
│   ├── OLCS Audit Trail
│   └── Monthly Board Financial Report
│
├── Inspectorate Readiness         ← Tier 2 (differentiator)
│   ├── WSE Preparation Pack
│   ├── SSE Data Summary
│   └── Prior Recommendations Tracker
│
├── SEN Provision                  ← Tier 2 (Expansion-B)
│   ├── SET Hours Tracker
│   ├── SNA Deployment Register
│   └── NCSE Review Data Pack
│
├── GDPR Compliance                ← Tier 2 (exists, surface it)
│   ├── SAR Status Dashboard
│   ├── Processing Records
│   └── Consent Register
│
├── SEAI Energy Reporting          ← Tier 3 (simple)
│   ├── Annual Energy Data Entry
│   └── Auto-populated school size data
│
├── Admissions Compliance          ← Tier 3 (extends existing)
│   ├── Annual Notice Generator
│   ├── Prior Year Stats
│   └── Timeline Tracker
│
└── Board of Management Pack       ← Tier 2 (differentiator)
    ├── Meeting Agenda Templates
    ├── Auto-generated Board Reports
    │   (attendance, behaviour, bullying, finance, safeguarding, admissions)
    └── Compliance Checklist per Meeting
```

### 2.3 Tiering Rationale

| Tier | Criteria | Domains |
|------|----------|---------|
| **Tier 1** (Must-have) | Statutory — schools face legal consequences or funding loss without compliance | DES Returns, P-POD/POD, Tusla, Child Safeguarding, Anti-Bullying |
| **Tier 2** (Should-have) | Operationally critical or strong differentiator | FSSU, Inspectorate Readiness, SEN, GDPR, Board Pack |
| **Tier 3** (Nice-to-have) | Low complexity, rounds out coverage | SEAI Energy, Admissions Compliance |

