## Part 6: Technical Considerations

### 6.1 Schema Additions (Preliminary)

- `regulatory_calendar_events` — Configurable deadlines per tenant per regulatory domain
- `regulatory_submissions` — Audit log of every regulatory submission (type, date, status, file hash)
- `tusla_absence_codes` — Mapping table for Tusla-specific absence categorisation
- `des_subject_codes` — DES canonical subject code master list
- `reduced_school_days` — Tracking students on reduced timetables (new Tusla obligation)
- `anti_bullying_incidents` — Extended categorisation for Bí Cineálta (may extend existing behaviour_incidents)
- `board_meeting_reports` — Generated/archived Board meeting compliance packs
- `ppod_sync_log` — P-POD sync status, errors, and history per student

### 6.2 New Backend Module

```
modules/regulatory/
├── regulatory.module.ts
├── regulatory-calendar/          # Deadline management
├── tusla/                        # SAR, AAR, notifications
├── des-returns/                  # Files A-E, Form TL, DTR
├── ppod/                         # P-POD sync engine
├── board-pack/                   # Board meeting report generation
├── compliance-dashboard/         # Aggregation layer
└── dto/
```

### 6.3 Worker Jobs

- `regulatory:deadline-check` — Daily cron checking approaching deadlines, sending reminders
- `regulatory:tusla-threshold-scan` — Check students approaching 20-day absence threshold
- `regulatory:des-returns-generate` — Background generation of encrypted DES files
- `regulatory:ppod-sync` — Scheduled P-POD data sync
- `regulatory:board-pack-generate` — Pre-meeting Board pack generation

