| Tusla SAR electronic format | `portal.tusla.ie` documentation | High |
| DES subject code master list | DES / DTR system | High |
| FSSU chart of accounts spec | `fssu.ie` documentation | Medium |
| SEAI M&R-2030 data format | `seai.ie` | Low |
| Bí Cineálta annual DES submission format | Circular 0055/2024 detail | Medium |

### 7.2 SMIS Framework Application

All Tier 1 regulatory integrations should be built **before** applying to the SMIS Framework (HEAnet/Asiera). Current approved suppliers: Aladdin, Compass, Databiz, IST Group, Tyro, VSware. The application requires demonstrating:
- Proven product
- Irish data residency
- GDPR compliance
- Statutory reporting capabilities
- Security certifications
- Ideally 3–5 pilot school references

### 7.3 Recommended Immediate Actions

1. **Contact `ppodhelpdesk@education.gov.ie`** — Request vendor integration documentation for P-POD API/sync protocol
2. **Obtain DES September Return format specs** — Either through DES directly or by studying VSware's published help docs on the process
3. **Review `portal.tusla.ie` user guide** — Understand SAR submission format
4. **Review Circular 0055/2024** — Full text of Bí Cineálta procedures for implementation detail
5. **Engage pilot schools** — Understand their current regulatory workflow pain points

